author: IGN
description:
In today's Daily Fix:
Dead Space's original co-creator wants another crack at the franchise. Glen Schofield, who worked on the original Dead Space, thinks it's possible a new entry in the series could happen in light of the industry-shaking EA buyout. In fact, according to Schofield, he's already been making calls to try and make a fourth Dead Space happen. In other news, Quantic Dream has announced a new 3v3 multiplayer game called Spellcasters Chroncles. Quantic Dream is mainly known for single-player narratives like Detroit: Become Human and Heavy Rain. They also have Star Wars Eclipse still in development, although it's been years since they've shown off anything from that game. And finally, legendary and controversial game designer Tomonobu Itagaki has passed away at age 58. He left a final message on his Facebook page, which was posted in the event of his death. Itagaki was behind the Ninja Gaiden revival in 2004 and the fighting game franchise Dead or Alive. His last game as a
title: Dead Space 4 Could Happen Under New EA Ownership, Series Creator "Making Calls" - IGN Daily Fix

author: IGN
description:
When you get a spontaneous call from the president of Nintendo of America, you don’t ask too many questions. You just take the call.

Chris Maple was being asked to make a new logo for Pokemon, which at the time existed only in Japan as Pocket Monsters Red and Pocket Monsters Green. Nintendo wanted to release the game in the West with a Blue version and, later, a Yellow Pikachu Edition. But the company wanted a new logo to fit the rebrand from “Pocket Monsters” to “Pokémon”, and was struggling to find someone to nail the look. Maple wasn’t given any instructions on what Nintendo was looking for, though, he says. Just one parameter: he had just one month to make it.

Meet Chris Maple, a Seattle-based designer who unwittingly stumbled into creating one of the most iconic logos in the world.

#IGN
title: How The Iconic Pokemon Logo Was Created

description:
Check out 13 minutes of Spellcaster Chronicles gameplay, the latest game from Quantic Dream (Heavy Rain, Star Wars: Eclipse), coming soon to PC.

Spellcasters Chronicles is a free-to-play, team-based, 3rd-person action-strategy game from French developers Quantic Dream. 

Play as a powerful mage and team up with your allies in epic 3v3 battles. Unleash devastating spells, apply buffs to your allies and even change the environment to your advantage! Command your army of hundreds from the skies, as you fly around the environment, engaging in aerial combat and tactical decision making to secure victory. 

Build your play-style by equipping spells that suit your strategy from a comprehensive list of over 50 spells from seven schools of magic. With a wide roster of creatures ranging from skeletons to dragons, match your spells to your army units for maximum dominance of the field.

#IGN #SpellcastersChronicles #FreeToPlay

author: IGN
description:
Battlefield 6's multiplayer reviewed by Justin Koreis on PC, also available on Xbox and PlayStation.

Battlefield 6’s multiplayer action is expertly crafted, wrapped in a wonderful layer of destructibility that both looks great and materially affects the flow of combat. The gunplay is excellent, with weapons that are accurate enough to reward skilled shooting, but have just enough sway to promote a bit of careful thought while you take aim. I wish the early progression didn’t delay the fun of loadout building quite as much, and a few of the maps would benefit from some rebalancing, but most of the options play really well overall. Besides, those are minor gripes with what is otherwise a great time. Like a precision shot from my trusty M2010 sniper rifle, this one’s a hit.

#IGN #Gaming #Battlefield6
title: Battlefield 6 Multiplayer Review
